max_tokens_sample.question: What are the pairs of teachers and students who are in the same class? Give me the pairs of their details.

min_tokens_sample.question: What is the name of the oldest pilot?
min_tokens_sample.final_sql: SELECT pilot_name FROM PilotSkills WHERE age = (SELECT MAX(age) FROM PilotSkills);

samples.question: Show all staff names who have been both speaker and sponsor in some conference.
samples.final_sql: SELECT DISTINCT s.name FROM staff s JOIN conference_participation cp1 ON s.staff_ID = cp1.staff_ID JOIN conference_participation cp2 ON s.staff_ID = cp2.staff_ID AND cp1.Conference_ID = cp2.Conference_ID WHERE cp1.role = 'speaker' AND cp2.role = 'sponsor';

samples.question: Give the ids for goods that have Apricot flavor and have a price lower than 5 dollars.
samples.final_sql: SELECT Id FROM goods WHERE Flavor = 'Apricot' AND Price < 5;

samples.question: Give the full names of artists who have created paintings and sculptures.
samples.final_sql: SELECT DISTINCT a.fname, a.lname FROM Artists a JOIN Paintings p ON a.artistID = p.painterID JOIN Sculptures s ON a.artistID = s.sculptorID;

samples.question: Show me the distance between Boston and Newark.
samples.final_sql: SELECT d.distance FROM Direct_distance AS d JOIN City AS c1 ON d.city1_code = c1.city_code JOIN City AS c2 ON d.city2_code = c2.city_code WHERE c1.city_name = 'Boston' AND c2.city_name = 'Newark';

samples.question: How many buildings are there?
samples.final_sql: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM building;

samples.question: Which planet has total weight of shipment greater than 30? List planet name.
samples.final_sql: SELECT p.Name FROM Planet p JOIN Shipment s ON p.PlanetID = s.Planet JOIN Package pk ON s.ShipmentID = pk.Shipment GROUP BY p.Name HAVING SUM(pk.Weight) > 30;

samples.question: Show the customers with total quantity of order bigger than 1.
samples.final_sql: SELECT c.Customer_ID, c.Name, SUM(co.Quantity) AS Total_Quantity FROM customer AS c JOIN customer_order AS co ON c.Customer_ID = co.Customer_ID GROUP BY c.Customer_ID, c.Name HAVING SUM(co.Quantity) > 1;

samples.question: What are the product type code with at least two products?
samples.final_sql: SELECT product_type_code FROM Products GROUP BY product_type_code HAVING COUNT(product_id) >= 2;

samples.question: Return the maximum and minimum enrollment across all institutions.
samples.final_sql: SELECT MAX(Enrollment) AS Max_Enrollment, MIN(Enrollment) AS Min_Enrollment FROM institution;

samples.question: What is the number of all packages that Leo Wong sent?
samples.final_sql: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM Package JOIN Client ON Package.Sender = Client.AccountNumber WHERE Client.Name = 'Leo Wong';

samples.question: What is the average card credit of customers with membership level higher than 1?
samples.final_sql: SELECT AVG(Card_Credit) FROM customer WHERE Level_of_Membership > 1;

samples.question: List all address ids and address details.
samples.final_sql: SELECT address_id, address_details FROM Addresses;

samples.question: Give the flavors of Cakes that are not available for Tart.
samples.final_sql: SELECT DISTINCT g1.Flavor FROM goods AS g1 WHERE g1.Food = 'cake' AND g1.Flavor NOT IN (SELECT g2.Flavor FROM goods AS g2 WHERE g2.Food = 'tart');

samples.question: Show the book title and purchase price of the book that has had the greatest amount in orders.
samples.final_sql: SELECT Book.Title, Book.PurchasePrice FROM Book JOIN Books_Order ON Book.ISBN = Books_Order.ISBN WHERE Books_Order.amount = (SELECT MAX(amount) FROM Books_Order);

samples.question: Find the first names and number of works of all artists who have at least two paintings?
samples.final_sql: SELECT fname, COUNT(paintingID) AS num_paintings FROM Artists JOIN Paintings ON artistID = painterID GROUP BY artistID HAVING num_paintings >= 2;

samples.question: What are the codes of warehouses that have more boxes than their capacity?
samples.final_sql: SELECT Warehouses.Code FROM Warehouses JOIN Boxes ON Warehouses.Code = Boxes.Warehouse GROUP BY Warehouses.Code HAVING COUNT(Boxes.Code) > Warehouses.Capacity;

samples.question: Show ids for all female (sex is F) students living in state PA.
samples.final_sql: SELECT Student.StuID FROM Student JOIN City ON Student.city_code = City.city_code WHERE Student.Sex = 'F' AND City.state = 'PA';

samples.question: Find the name of the publisher whose monthly profit is the highest.
samples.final_sql: SELECT p.Name FROM press p ORDER BY p.Month_Profits_billion DESC LIMIT 1;

samples.question: What is the total shipments in each planet? List the planet name and total shipments.
samples.final_sql: SELECT Planet.Name, COUNT(Shipment.ShipmentID) AS TotalShipments FROM Planet JOIN Shipment ON Planet.PlanetID = Shipment.Planet GROUP BY Planet.PlanetID, Planet.Name;

samples.question: find the average age of authors for each gender.
samples.final_sql: SELECT Gender, AVG(Age) AS Average_Age FROM author GROUP BY Gender;

samples.question: Find the biographical data and event date for students who participated in any events.
samples.final_sql: SELECT Students.bio_data, Student_Events.event_date FROM Students JOIN Student_Events ON Students.student_id = Student_Events.student_id;

samples.question: Show the names of club leaders and the names of clubs they joined.
What are the first names of all artists who have at least two paintings, and how many works did each create?
samples.final_sql: SELECT a.fname, COUNT(p.paintingID) AS painting_count FROM Artists a JOIN Paintings p ON a.artistID = p.painterID GROUP BY a.artistID HAVING COUNT(p.paintingID) >= 2;

samples.question: What are the names of all sailors with a higher rating than every sailor named Luis?
samples.final_sql: SELECT S1.name FROM Sailors S1 WHERE S1.rating > (SELECT MAX(S2.rating) FROM Sailors S2 WHERE S2.name = 'Luis');

samples.question: Find the names of spokesmen who have served some district before 2004.
samples.final_sql: SELECT DISTINCT s.Name FROM spokesman s JOIN spokesman_district sd ON s.Spokesman_ID = sd.Spokesman_ID WHERE sd.Start_year < 2004;

samples.question: What is the total weight for all packages that Leo Wong sent?
samples.final_sql: SELECT SUM(Package.Weight) FROM Package JOIN Client ON Package.Sender = Client.AccountNumber WHERE Client.Name = 'Leo Wong';

samples.question: List the order date of the orders who are placed by customers with at least 2 payment methods.
samples.final_sql: SELECT Orders.date_order_placed FROM Orders JOIN Customers ON Orders.customer_id = Customers.customer_id JOIN Customer_Payment_Methods ON Customers.customer_id = Customer_Payment_Methods.customer_id GROUP BY Orders.order_id HAVING COUNT(DISTINCT Customer_Payment_Methods.payment_method_code) >= 2;

samples.question: Calculate total weight of package shipped on Mars.
samples.final_sql: SELECT SUM(P.Weight) AS TotalWeight FROM Package P JOIN Shipment S ON P.Shipment = S.ShipmentID JOIN Planet PL ON S.Planet = PL.PlanetID WHERE PL.Name = 'Mars';

samples.question: What are the ids and names of all customers?
samples.final_sql: SELECT customer_id, customer_name FROM Customers;

samples.question: Where is the plane F-14 Fighter located?
What are the statuses, dates, and shipment dates for all invoices?
samples.final_sql: SELECT Invoices.invoice_status_code, Invoices.invoice_date, Shipments.shipment_date FROM Invoices LEFT JOIN Shipments ON Invoices.invoice_number = Shipments.invoice_number;

samples.question: Show all university names without a major with rank 1?
samples.final_sql: SELECT u.University_Name FROM university u WHERE u.University_ID NOT IN (SELECT mr.University_ID FROM major_ranking mr WHERE mr.Rank = 1);

samples.question: What are the ids and flavors of cakes, ordered by flavor?
samples.final_sql: SELECT Id, Flavor FROM goods WHERE Food = 'cake' ORDER BY Flavor;

samples.question: Show all product names with price higher than the average.
samples.final_sql: SELECT product_name FROM Products WHERE product_price > (SELECT AVG(product_price) FROM Products);

samples.question: What is the distance between BAL and CHI?
samples.final_sql: SELECT distance FROM Direct_distance WHERE city1_code = 'BAL' AND city2_code = 'CHI' OR city1_code = 'CHI' AND city2_code = 'BAL';

samples.question: How many meetings are there for each client id?
samples.final_sql: SELECT client_id, COUNT(*) AS meeting_count FROM Meetings GROUP BY client_id;

samples.question: Show names of players from the club with manager "Sam Allardyce".
samples.final_sql: SELECT player.Name FROM player JOIN club ON player.Club_ID = club.Club_ID WHERE club.Manager = 'Sam Allardyce';

samples.question: Return the age category for the user who made the earliest search.
samples.final_sql: SELECT RAC.age_category_description FROM User_Searches US JOIN Users U ON US.user_id = U.user_id JOIN Ref_Age_Categories RAC ON U.age_category_code = RAC.age_category_code ORDER BY US.search_datetime ASC LIMIT 1;

samples.question: Which teacher teaches the most courses? Give me the id of the teacher and the number of courses he or she teaches.
samples.final_sql: SELECT teacher_id, COUNT(class_id) AS course_count FROM Classes GROUP BY teacher_id ORDER BY course_count DESC LIMIT 1;

samples.question: What is the id of every painting created before the oldest painting in gallery 240?
samples.final_sql: SELECT p1.paintingID FROM Paintings p1 WHERE p1.year < (SELECT MIN(p2.year) FROM Paintings p2 WHERE p2.location = '240')

samples.question: Show all book titles for books that have no orders.
samples.final_sql: SELECT Title FROM Book WHERE ISBN NOT IN (SELECT ISBN FROM Books_Order);

samples.question: What are the receipt numbers for a customer with the last name Logan who purchased a croissant?
samples.final_sql: SELECT receipts.ReceiptNumber FROM receipts JOIN customers ON receipts.CustomerId = customers.Id JOIN items ON receipts.ReceiptNumber = items.Receipt JOIN goods ON items.Item = goods.Id WHERE customers.LastName = 'Logan' AND goods.Food = 'croissant';

samples.question: List the names of regions that do not have any buildings.
samples.final_sql: SELECT region.Name FROM region LEFT JOIN building ON region.Region_ID = building.Region_ID WHERE building.Region_ID IS NULL;

samples.question: Find the valid answer text that appeared most frequently.
samples.final_sql: SELECT Valid_Answer_Text FROM Valid_Answers GROUP BY Valid_Answer_Text ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC LIMIT 1;

samples.question: From which countries are players who make more than 1200000 from?
samples.final_sql: SELECT DISTINCT player.Country FROM player WHERE player.Earnings > 1200000;

samples.question: How many clients are there?
samples.final_sql: SELECT COUNT(client_id) FROM Clients;

samples.question: What is the smallest number of packages received and by whom ?
samples.final_sql: SELECT Recipient, COUNT(*) AS PackageCount FROM Package GROUP BY Recipient ORDER BY PackageCount ASC LIMIT 1;

samples.question: List the driver makes that are associated with at least three drivers.
samples.final_sql: SELECT d.Make FROM driver d JOIN team_driver td ON d.Driver_ID = td.Driver_ID GROUP BY d.Make HAVING COUNT(d.Driver_ID) >= 3;

samples.question: What are the number of shipments managed and names of each manager?
samples.final_sql: SELECT e.Name, COUNT(s.ShipmentID) AS ShipmentCount FROM Employee e JOIN Shipment s ON e.EmployeeID = s.Manager GROUP BY e.Name;

samples.question: What is the first name of the sculptor with the greatest number of works?
samples.final_sql: SELECT fname FROM Artists JOIN Sculptures ON Artists.artistID = Sculptures.sculptorID GROUP BY sculptorID ORDER BY COUNT(sculptureID) DESC LIMIT 1;

samples.question: Find the countries where no driver come from.
samples.final_sql: SELECT c.Country FROM country c LEFT JOIN driver d ON c.Country = d.Country WHERE d.Driver_ID IS NULL;

samples.question: Show the names of customers and names of dishes they order.
samples.final_sql: SELECT customer.Name, customer_order.Dish_Name FROM customer JOIN customer_order ON customer.Customer_ID = customer_order.Customer_ID;

samples.question: Which venues and years did Columbia University have papers ?
samples.final_sql: SELECT DISTINCT Paper.venue, Paper.year FROM Paper JOIN Author_list ON Paper.paper_id = Author_list.paper_id JOIN Affiliation ON Author_list.affiliation_id = Affiliation.affiliation_id WHERE Affiliation.name = 'Columbia University';

samples.question: Show different manufacturers and the number of clubs they are associated with.
samples.final_sql: SELECT Manufacturer, COUNT(DISTINCT club.Club_ID) AS Club_Count FROM club GROUP BY Manufacturer;

samples.question: Give the ids of goods that are more than twice as expensive as the average good.
samples.final_sql: SELECT Id FROM goods WHERE Price > 2 * (SELECT AVG(Price) FROM goods);

samples.question: What are the package numbers and weights that are between 10 and 30?
samples.final_sql: SELECT PackageNumber, Weight FROM Package WHERE Weight BETWEEN 10 AND 30;

samples.question: How many books does each book series have? Return the counts and book series.
samples.final_sql: SELECT Book_Series, COUNT(Book_ID) AS Number_of_Books FROM book GROUP BY Book_Series;

samples.question: Find the location of the warehouses which store contents Rocks and Scissors.
samples.final_sql: SELECT DISTINCT Warehouses.Location FROM Warehouses JOIN Boxes ON Warehouses.Code = Boxes.Warehouse WHERE Boxes.Contents IN ('Rocks', 'Scissors');

samples.question: Show the three official languages that are most commonly spoken.
samples.final_sql: SELECT l.name, COUNT(*) AS count FROM official_languages ol JOIN languages l ON ol.language_id = l.id GROUP BY l.name ORDER BY count DESC LIMIT 3;

samples.question: Find the name of the theater that is playing the most number of movies.
samples.final_sql: SELECT Name FROM MovieTheaters GROUP BY Name ORDER BY COUNT(Movie) DESC LIMIT 1;

samples.question: Find the locations that have paintings created before 1885 and after 1930?
samples.final_sql: SELECT DISTINCT p1.location FROM Paintings AS p1 JOIN Paintings AS p2 ON p1.location = p2.location WHERE p1.year < 1885 AND p2.year > 1930;

samples.question: How many players have rank of the year smaller than 3?
samples.final_sql: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM player WHERE Rank_of_the_year < 3;

samples.question: What are the names of pilots between the ages of 30 and 40, ordered by age ascending?
samples.final_sql: SELECT pilot_name FROM PilotSkills WHERE age BETWEEN 30 AND 40 ORDER BY age ASC;

samples.question: Find the analytical layer type code that appears most often.
samples.final_sql: SELECT Analytical_Layer_Type_Code FROM Analytical_Layer GROUP BY Analytical_Layer_Type_Code ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC LIMIT 1;

samples.question: How many movies are playing in theaters?
samples.final_sql: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT Movies.Code) FROM Movies JOIN MovieTheaters ON Movies.Code = MovieTheaters.Movie;

samples.question: Return the id and detail for the agency with the most staff.
samples.final_sql: SELECT a.agency_id, a.agency_details FROM Agencies a JOIN Staff s ON a.agency_id = s.agency_id GROUP BY a.agency_id ORDER BY COUNT(s.staff_id) DESC LIMIT 1;

samples.question: How many staff do we have?
samples.final_sql: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM Staff;

samples.question: What are the earnings of players from either of the countries of Australia or Zimbabwe?
samples.final_sql: SELECT player.Earnings FROM player WHERE player.Country IN ('Australia', 'Zimbabwe');

samples.question: What are the pairs of teachers and students who are in the same class? Give me the pairs of their details.
What is the full name of the customer who visited on the earliest date?
samples.final_sql: SELECT FirstName || ' ' || LastName AS FullName FROM customers JOIN receipts ON customers.Id = receipts.CustomerId WHERE Date = (SELECT MIN(Date) FROM receipts);

samples.question: Find the name, rating and age of all sailors ordered by rating and age.
samples.final_sql: SELECT name, rating, age FROM Sailors ORDER BY rating, age;

samples.question: Which authors have published more than 1 book according to the database? Give me their names.
samples.final_sql: SELECT a.Name FROM author a JOIN book b ON a.Author_ID = b.Author_ID GROUP BY a.Author_ID HAVING COUNT(b.Book_ID) > 1;

samples.question: List the names of members in ascending order of age.
samples.final_sql: SELECT Name FROM member ORDER BY Age ASC;

samples.question: What is the title of the book that has been ordered the greatest number of times?
samples.final_sql: SELECT B.Title FROM Book B JOIN Books_Order BO ON B.ISBN = BO.ISBN GROUP BY B.Title ORDER BY SUM(BO.amount) DESC LIMIT 1;

samples.question: Show all document ids without a process.
samples.final_sql: SELECT document_id FROM Documents WHERE document_id NOT IN (SELECT document_id FROM Documents_Processes);

samples.question: Which collection have most number of documents? List collection name, id and number of documents.
samples.final_sql: SELECT c.Collection_ID, c.Collection_Name, COUNT(d.Document_Object_ID) AS Document_Count FROM Collections c JOIN Documents_in_Collections d ON c.Collection_ID = d.Collection_ID GROUP BY c.Collection_ID, c.Collection_Name ORDER BY Document_Count DESC LIMIT 1;

samples.question: Show the distinct addresses of buildings.
samples.final_sql: SELECT DISTINCT Address FROM building;

samples.question: How many item states are there in the orders?
samples.final_sql: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT order_item_status_code) FROM Order_Items;

samples.question: List the detail and id of the teacher who teaches the most courses.
samples.final_sql: SELECT t.teacher_id, t.teacher_details FROM Teachers t JOIN Classes c ON t.teacher_id = c.teacher_id GROUP BY t.teacher_id, t.teacher_details ORDER BY COUNT(c.class_id) DESC LIMIT 1;

samples.question: On which day did the bakery sell more than 100 dollars in total.
samples.final_sql: SELECT receipts.Date, SUM(goods.Price) AS TotalSales FROM receipts JOIN items ON receipts.ReceiptNumber = items.Receipt JOIN goods ON items.Item = goods.Id GROUP BY receipts.Date HAVING TotalSales > 100;

samples.question: How many stores are there in each neighborhood?
samples.final_sql: SELECT Neighborhood, COUNT(DISTINCT Store_ID) AS Store_Count FROM store GROUP BY Neighborhood;

samples.question: Show all client names who have orders for "Pride and Prejudice".
samples.final_sql: SELECT DISTINCT Client.Name FROM Client JOIN Orders ON Client.IdClient = Orders.IdClient JOIN Books_Order ON Orders.IdOrder = Books_Order.IdOrder JOIN Book ON Books_Order.ISBN = Book.ISBN WHERE Book.Title = 'Pride and Prejudice';

samples.question: Give the stadium of the institution which is the greatest enrollment.
samples.final_sql: SELECT Stadium FROM institution ORDER BY Enrollment DESC LIMIT 1;

samples.question: What is the name of the oldest pilot?
samples.final_sql: SELECT pilot_name FROM PilotSkills WHERE age = (SELECT MAX(age) FROM PilotSkills);

samples.question: List the names of customers that do not have any order.
samples.final_sql: SELECT Name FROM customer WHERE Customer_ID NOT IN (SELECT Customer_ID FROM customer_order);

samples.question: For each location, what are the total, average, and maximum capacities of warehouses?
samples.final_sql: SELECT Location, SUM(Capacity) AS TotalCapacity, AVG(Capacity) AS AverageCapacity, MAX(Capacity) AS MaximumCapacity FROM Warehouses GROUP BY Location;

samples.question: what is the total package weight for each planet, list its name ?
samples.final_sql: SELECT Planet.Name, SUM(Package.Weight) AS TotalWeight FROM Planet JOIN Shipment ON Planet.PlanetID = Shipment.Planet JOIN Package ON Shipment.ShipmentID = Package.Shipment GROUP BY Planet.PlanetID, Planet.Name;

samples.question: How many addresses do we have?
samples.final_sql: SELECT COUNT(address_id) FROM Addresses;

samples.question: How many cities are in each state?
samples.final_sql: SELECT state, COUNT(DISTINCT city_code) AS city_count FROM City GROUP BY state;

samples.question: What is the payment method that most customers use?
samples.final_sql: SELECT payment_method_code FROM Customer_Payment_Methods GROUP BY payment_method_code ORDER BY COUNT(customer_id) DESC LIMIT 1;

samples.question: find the number of authors who are older than 30 for each gender.
samples.final_sql: SELECT Gender, COUNT(*) FROM author WHERE Age > 30 GROUP BY Gender;

samples.question: Which teachers have taught the student with the earliest transcript issuance? List the teacher details.
samples.final_sql: SELECT DISTINCT t.teacher_details FROM Teachers t JOIN Classes c ON t.teacher_id = c.teacher_id JOIN Students s ON c.student_id = s.student_id JOIN Transcripts tr ON s.student_id = tr.student_id WHERE tr.date_of_transcript = (SELECT MIN(date_of_transcript) FROM Transcripts);

samples.question: Find the distinct titles of all the paintings that have a longer height than some painting on canvas?
How many courses do teachers teach at most? Also find the id of the teacher who teaches the most.
samples.final_sql: SELECT teacher_id, COUNT(class_id) AS course_count FROM Classes GROUP BY teacher_id ORDER BY course_count DESC LIMIT 1;

samples.question: For each city, what is the the city code and sum of distances from each?
samples.final_sql: SELECT c.city_code, SUM(d.distance) AS total_distance FROM City c JOIN Direct_distance d ON c.city_code = d.city1_code OR c.city_code = d.city2_code GROUP BY c.city_code;

samples.question: Find the name of authors who have never published a paper in ACL.
samples.final_sql: SELECT DISTINCT a.name FROM Author a WHERE a.author_id NOT IN (SELECT al.author_id FROM Author_list al JOIN Paper p ON al.paper_id = p.paper_id WHERE p.venue = 'ACL')

samples.question: How many vehicles have maximum top speed?
samples.final_sql: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM vehicle WHERE Top_Speed = (SELECT MAX(Top_Speed) FROM vehicle);

samples.question: List all book titles which have highest purchase prices .
samples.final_sql: SELECT Title FROM Book WHERE PurchasePrice = (SELECT MAX(PurchasePrice) FROM Book);

samples.question: What is the detail of document subset with name 'Best for 2000'?
samples.final_sql: SELECT Document_Subset_Details FROM Document_Subsets WHERE Document_Subset_Name = 'Best for 2000';

samples.question: Find the number of all distinct contents in all the boxes.
samples.final_sql: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT Contents) FROM Boxes;
